<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-12-23T08:34:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-12-23T08:34:00-05:00" n="245" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d245">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">861.00/5952: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The President of the Technical Board</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SJF1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Stevens</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Harbin</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-12-23T22:00:00+08:26"><hi rend="italic">December 23,
                                        1919, 10 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received December 23, 9
                                a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Capture Tomsk and 6,000 soldiers with a general by the anti-<persName corresp="#p_KAAV1">Kolchak</persName> forces officially confirmed.
                            Nothing evacuated from the city. Rumor not yet confirmed capture of
                            Taiga with some American Red Cross people cut off.</p>
                        <closer><signed><persName corresp="#p_SJF1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Stevens</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>